Pinguino IDE Installation & Use Instructions
*************************************************

Copyright (C) 2008 Jean-Pierre MANDON <jp.mandon@gmail.com>

This file is free documentation; you have unlimited permission to copy, 
distribute and modify it.

Pinguino is an arduino like environment built in Python.
It is a complete package with compiler, assembler, linker and bootloader, nothing to install.
Pinguino is compatible with arduino/wiring langage.

dependencies:

Linux 		libusb
			python 2.5
			wxpython 2.8

Pinguino is based on open source software:
	compiler		SDCC 2.9.0		http://sdcc.sourceforge.net/
	asm/linker		GPUTILS			http://gputils.sourceforge.net/
	bootloader		VASCO project	http://vasco.gforge.enseeiht.fr/
	IDE				Python			http://www.python.org/
			
Contributions, bug reports and questions are welcome.
jp.mandon@gmail.com
